"v.闲荡，嬉戏 【英】 v. 闲荡，嬉戏 (to waste time; loiter; trifle) 【考】 dally : time / squander : money(浪费时间/浪费金钱) 【记】 可以和'daily'(每日 的)一起记，dally time away (蹉跎光阴) v. 蹉跎(光阴); 闲荡 = dawdle; (好色地)嬉戏 = trifle = toy = loiter = flirt; 【记】dally可以但是不能daily(adj 每日的); dally away 蹉跎光阴读: 大理, 段誉在大理dally 【参】dalliance(v 戏弄, 调情 = dallying = flirting = toying) 【类】dally: time = squander: money 浪费时间 = 浪费金钱 【记】咱这有志青年可不能daily每天蹉跎光阴，寻花问柳的玩乐；音:代理 (跨国公司驻中国)代理可是整天玩，虚度时光可也过得挺好啊 dally (v.)  c.1300, ""to talk, converse,"" possibly from Anglo-French dalier ""to amuse oneself,"" of uncertain origin. Sense of ""waste time"" emerged by late 14c. Related: Dallied; dallying."
